The article discusses the steps taken by the Obama Administration to reduce harmful air pollution while promoting economic growth. It highlights the benefits of clean air for public health and the environment, citing a report by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) that estimates the direct benefits of the Clean Air Act to reach nearly $2 trillion in 2020, exceeding the costs by more than 30 to one. The article also mentions the achievements of the Obama Administration in doubling fuel efficiency for cars and light-duty trucks, setting standards for medium and heavy-duty trucks, cutting pollution from power plants and industrial sources, and reducing toxic air pollution. Additionally, it mentions the investment in clean energy through the Recovery Act and the commitment to energy efficiency in the transportation sector and built environment.